  <title>Create a Report</title>

  <p>To create a report:</p>
  <steps>
    <item><p>Log in to the Control Panel.</p></item>
    <item><p>Click the <gui style="tab">Report</gui> tab.</p></item>
    <item><p>Select <guiseq><gui style="menu">File</gui><gui style="menuitem">New</gui></guiseq>, or press <keyseq><key>Ctrl</key><key>N</key></keyseq>, or click <gui style="button">New</gui> in the toolbar to open the Report Assistant.</p></item>
    <item><p>Follow the instructions of the Report Assistant.</p></item>
  </steps>

  <note style="important">
    <p>In regular reports, the start and end date should either be the first and 15th day of the same month, or the 16th and last day of the same month.</p>
    <p>The end date should always be after the start date.</p>
  </note>

  <note style="important">
    <p>In overtime reports, make sure that holidays are properly set before creating the report.</p>
  </note>

